completion.trace.snippet:
- `trace 'all': 1`: All SolidCAM and user procedures will be traced with minimum trace information available.
- `trace '@proc':level`: Only procedure @proc will be traced, either it is SolidCAM's or user's one.
 - `level = 0`: no trace information.
 - `level=1`: procedure routine name will be printed.
 - `level > 1`: trace data in produced
completion.new.region.snippet: define `new #region`. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.or.operator: `or` return `true` if any of its operands is `true`
completion.eq.operator: `eq (or '==')` return `true` if both operands are equal
completion.ne.operator: `ne (or '<>')` return `true` if both operands are different
completion.le.operator: `le (or '<=')` return `true` if first operand is less than or equal to the second
completion.lt.operator: `lt (or '<' )` return `true` if first operand is less than the second
completion.ge.operator: `ge (or '>=')` return `true` if first operand is greater than or equal to the second
completion.gt.operator: `gt (or '>' )` return `true` if first operand is greater than the second
completion.active.function: `active(variable)` returns `true/false (1/0)` if variable is *active*. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.change.function: `change(variable)` returns `true/false (1/0)` if variable *was change*. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.even.function: `even(number)` is `true` only if the `number` *is even*. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.odd.function: `odd(number)` is true only if the `number` *is odd*. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.date.function: `date` returns the string value of the current date in the format `DD-MM-YYYY`
completion.dup.function: `dup(string, count)` returns a string value, consisting of the string `string` duplicated `count` times. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.instr.function: `instr(str, substr, val)` searches for the appearance of the `substr` in `str` from the `val` column and returns its position from the beginning of `str`. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.left.function: `left(str, num)` returns the sub-string which consists of `num` left characters of `str`. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.lower.function: `lower(string)` returns the same `string`, where all upper case (capital) letters (a-z) are replaced by their lower case equivalent (a-z). The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.replace.function: `replace(str, oldstr, newstr , k)` replace the `k` appearance of the `oldstr` in `str` with `newstr` and returns the `str`. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.rev.function: `rev(string)` returns the same `string` while reversing the order of its characters. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.right.function: `right(str, num)` returns the sub-string which consists of the `num` right characters of `str`. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.space.function: `space(len)` returns a string of blanks (spaces) of length `len`
completion.strlen.function: `strlen(string)` returns the length of the `string`, i.e. The number of characters in the string. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.substr.function: `substr(string, from, len)` returns the sub-string starting in the `string` from position `from`, and with length `len`. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.time.function: `time` returns the string value of the current time in the format 'HH:MM:SS'
completion.tonum.function: `tonum(string)` converts the number represented in the `string` from string format to a numeric format. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.tostr.function: `tostr(number:format)` converts the `number` into string notation according to the format specification `format`. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.trim.function: `trim(string)` returns the same string as in the `string`, but removes all its trailing blanks. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.upper.function: `upper(string)` returns the same `string`, where all the lower case letters (a-z) are replaced by their upper case (capital) equivalent (A-Z). The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.abs.function: `abs(number)` returns the arc cosine of the `number`. The angle returned is in degrees in the range (0, 180). The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.acos.function: `acos(number)` returns the arc cosine of the `number`. The angle returned is in degrees in the range (0, 180). The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.adims.function: `adims(array)` returns the number of dimensions of the array. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.alen.function: `alen(array, dim)` returns the number of elements in the required dimension of the `array`. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.ang.function: `ang(x, y)` returns the angle between vector to the point and the positive direction of the `X axis`. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.asin.function: `asin(number)` returns the arc sine of the `number`. The angle returned is in degrees in the range (-90, 90). The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.asize.function: `asize(array)` returns the number of elements in the array. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.atan.function: `atan(number)` returns the arc tangent of the `number`. The angle returned is in degrees in the range (-90, 90). The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.atan2.function: `atan2(y, x)` returns the angle defined by the point and the positive direction of the `X axis`
completion.cos.function: `cos(angle)` returns the cosine value of the `angle`. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.dist.function: `dist(x, y)` returns the distance between the point and the origin of the axis system (point (0,0) ). `dist (x, y)` is equivalent to `sqrt(x*x + y*y)`
completion.exp.function: `exp(number)` returns the value of e (the base of natural logarithms) to the power of `number`. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.frac.function: `frac(number)` returns the fraction part of the `number`. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.int.function: `int(number)` returns the integer part of the `number`. The value is truncated, not rounded. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.log.function: `log(number)` returns the value of the natural logarithm of the `number`. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.log10.function: `log10(number)` returns the value of the base 10 logarithm of the `number`. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.mod.function: `mod(a, b)` returns the remainder R of a/b
completion.norm360.function: `norm360(number)` returns the normalized angle of the parameter in the range (0,360). The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.pow.function: `pow(b, p)` returns the value of `b` to the power of `p`
completion.round.function: `round(number, dig)` returns the number rounded to the required number of digits either after or before the decimal point. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.round2val.function: `round2val(c, d)` returns `c` rounded to smallest multiple of `d`. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.sign.function: `sign(number)` returns an integer number, representing the `sign` of the `number`. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.sin.function: `sin(angle)` returns the sine value of the `angle`. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.sqrt.function: `sqrt(number)` returns the square root of the `number` is equivalent to `pow(number, 0.5)`. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.square.function: `square(number)` returns the value of the `number` squared. it is equivalent to `pow(number, 2)`. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.tan.function: `tan(angle)` returns the tangent value of the `angle`. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.todeg.function: `todeg(angle)` returns the `angle` (given in radians) into its equivalent in degrees. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.torad.function: `torad(angle)` returns the `angle` (given in degrees) into its equivalent in radians. The selected text can be wrapped.
completion.doc.job_type.value: One of the possible values of the job_type variable
completion.doc.tool_type.value: One of the possible values of the tool_type variable
parser.variable.lenght.error: the length of the variable must not exceed 60 characters
parser.variable.first.letter.error: the first character must not be a digit
parser.variable.other.letter.error: a variable name must consist of digits, letters and the '_' symbol.
